condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Bidders Conference | Description :The Recipient shall, not later than one (1) month after the Effective Date,organize a bidders conference with a view to addressing, among others, measures for preventing fraud and corruption in theProject, under terms of reference acceptable to the Association | Due Date :28-Aug-2015
Finance Agreement :Contracts Committee. | Description :The Recipient has, through the Project Implementing Entity, established theContracts Committee | Due Date :01-Apr-2014

Finance Agreement :Filing and Recording System | Description :The Recipient shall, not later than twelve (12) months after theEffective Date, update its procurement filing and record keeping system, in form and substance acceptable to the Association | DueDate :31-Dec-2014

Finance Agreement :Office Space | Description :The Recipient shall, not later than twelve (12) months after the Effective Date,acquire additional and appropriate office space for PDU staff, under terms of reference acceptable to the Association | Due Date:31-Dec-2014

Finance Agreement :Procurement and Environmental and Social Management Specialist at Min. of Lands. | Description :The Recipientshall, through MLHUD, not later than one (1) month after the Effective Date, appoint in accordance with the provisions of SectionIII of Schedule 2 to the Financing Agreement, and thereafter maintain at all times during Project implementation, a procurementspecialist and an environmental and social management specialist, all with qualifications, experience and terms of reference acc |Due Date :18-Nov-2013

Finance Agreement :Project Steering Committee and Project Technical Committee. | Description :The Recipient has, through MoFPED,established the Project Steering Committee and Project Technical Committee, respectively, each in accordance with the provisions ofSection I.A.2 and I.A.3, respectively, of Schedule 2 to the Financing Agreement | Due Date :29-Aug-2013

Finance Agreement :Project Coordination Unit | Description :The Project Implementing Entity shall, not later than three (3) monthsafter the Effective Date, establish and thereafter maintain,at all times during the implementation of the Project, the ProjectCoordination Unit (“PCU”), to be responsible for prompt and efficient oversight (including day to day implementation, coordinationand management) of activities under its Respective Part of the Project | Due Date :31-Oct-2014

Finance Agreement :Project Operations Manual | Description :The Recipient has prepared and adopted the Project Operations Manual(including arrangements on financial management, procurement management procedures and a Matching Grants Manual), in accordancewith the provisions of Section I.C of Schedule 2 to the Financing Agreement. | Due Date :30-Jan-2014

Finance Agreement :Project Technical Specialists | Description :The Recipient has, through: (i) MLHUD, appointed a financialmanagement specialist, in accordance with the provisions of Section I.A.1 of Schedule 2 to the Financing Agreement; and (ii) theProject Implementing Entity, appointed a procurement specialist and a financial management specialist, in accordance with theprovisions of Section III.C of Schedule 2 to the Financing Agreement | Due Date :16-Jun-2014

Finance Agreement :Quantity Surveyor and Civil Engineer at Min. of Lands. | Description :The Recipient shall, through MLHUD, notlater than six (6) months after the Effective Date, appoint in accordance with the provisions of Section III of Schedule 2 to theFinancing Agreement, and thereafter maintain at all times during Project implementation, a quantity surveyor and a civil engineer,all with qualifications, experience and terms of reference acceptable to the Association | Due Date :17-Mar-2014

Finance Agreement :Subsidiary Agreement | Description :The Subsidiary Agreement, in form and substance satisfactory to theAssociation, has been executed on behalf of the Recipient and the Project Implementing Entity. | Due Date :28-Mar-2014

Finance Agreement :Training of PDU Staff. | Description :The Recipient shall, not later than six (6) months after the EffectiveDate, provide procurement training for PDU staff, under terms of reference acceptable to the Association | Due Date :31-Dec-2014
